title: The G-string Horror (2012)
description: When a production company starts shooting a horror film in a 100 year old...and actually haunted...Sid Grauman built movie palace turned strip club in San Francisco, the 'inhabitants' revolt and take over the movie for their own purposes with bizarre and shocking results. The G-string Horror has been described by one blogger as 'an independent, European-style surrealist film with great horror exploitation values'. 'Magical realism meets cinema verite meets George Romero', said another. A disclaimer before the main titles warns that...'Parts of the film...may induce unpredictable paranormal states. Viewer discretion strongly advised,'
